      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation through the full simulation chain producing NIH uncertainty bounds at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was initiated but only inlet flow rate and rotational speed were treated as uncertain inputs. Hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta in Giersiepen relation) were held fixed despite known variability. Achieved level 2 versus required level 5; gap flagged as epistemic."
